## Module 1: STAR Router — Dynamic Layer Skipping (DySL)

> **Nguồn cảm hứng**: Mixture-of-Depths (Raposo et al., 2024) + Spatial-Temporal Aware Routing
> 
> **Code**: [STARRouter](file:///d:/EyetechCode/finetune_dynamic_lora_prunning_snapflow.py#L86-L150)

### 1.1. Ý tưởng

SmolVLA sử dụng 16 VLM layers (đã skip 16/32 từ SmolLM2 gốc). Trong đó:
- **8 layers đầu (L0-L7)**: luôn chạy (fixed) — chứa cross-modal alignment quan trọng
- **8 layers sau (L8-L15)**: có thể skip — STAR Router quyết định frame-by-frame

### 1.2. Công thức toán học

**Input features** cho router:

$$\mathbf{x} = [\bar{\mathbf{h}}_{\text{pool}} \;;\; E_{\text{view}} \;;\; \|\Delta \mathbf{s}\|]  \in \mathbb{R}^{d+2}$$

Trong đó:
- $\bar{\mathbf{h}}_{\text{pool}} = \frac{1}{N}\sum_{i=1}^{N} \mathbf{e}_i^{\text{img}} \in \mathbb{R}^{d}$ — mean pooling của visual embeddings
- $E_{\text{view}} = \text{Mean}(\text{Var}_{\text{tokens}}(\mathbf{e}^{\text{img}})) \in \mathbb{R}$ — proxy cho visual entropy
- $\|\Delta \mathbf{s}\| = \|\mathbf{s}_t - \mathbf{s}_{t-1}\| \in \mathbb{R}$ — tốc độ thay đổi robot state

**Gate network** (MLP 2 lớp):

$$\mathbf{g}_{\text{logits}} = \mathbf{W}_2 \cdot \text{SiLU}(\mathbf{W}_1 \cdot \mathbf{x} + \mathbf{b}_1) + \mathbf{b}_2 \in \mathbb{R}^{8}$$

Bias $\mathbf{b}_2$ được khởi tạo = 2.0 (để sigmoid > 0.5 → mặc định KEEP layer).

**Training** — Gumbel-Softmax (differentiable binary):

$$\text{logits}_{2\text{class}} = \begin{bmatrix} 0 & g_i \end{bmatrix} \quad \text{(skip vs keep)}$$

$$\mathbf{g} = \text{GumbelSoftmax}(\text{logits}_{2\text{class}}, \tau)[..., 1]$$

Trong đó $\tau$ giảm dần: $\tau = 1.0 \to 0.1$ (annealing từ soft → hard decision).

**Inference** — Hard threshold:

$$g_i = \mathbb{1}[\sigma(g_{\text{logits}, i}) > 0.5]$$

**Gate loss** (regularization — khuyến khích skip nhiều hơn):

$$\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}} = \frac{1}{8}\sum_{i=1}^{8} g_i \qquad \text{(mean gate activation)}$$

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Minimizing $\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}}$ = khuyến khích $g_i \to 0$ = skip nhiều layers hơn. Trọng số $\lambda_{\text{cost}} = 0.001$ kiểm soát mức độ aggressive của skip.

### 1.3. Kết quả thực tế

Từ visualization:
- **Skip frequency = 100%** cho tất cả L8-L15
- **Active layers = 8/16** (chỉ dùng 8 fixed layers)
- Router học được rằng với task pick-place đơn giản, 8 layers đầu đã đủ thông tin

---

## Module 2: Action-Aware Dynamic Token Pruning (ADP)

> **Nguồn cảm hứng**: VLA-Pruner (Song et al., 2025) + FastV (Chen et al., 2024)
> 
> **Code**: [ActionAwareTokenPruner](file:///d:/EyetechCode/finetune_dynamic_lora_prunning_snapflow.py#L153-L232)

### 2.1. Ý tưởng

Khi robot di chuyển nhanh (coarse manipulation) → không cần nhìn chi tiết → prune visual tokens.  
Khi robot di chuyển chậm (fine manipulation) → cần precision cao → giữ tất cả tokens.

### 2.2. Công thức toán học

**End-effector velocity** (proxy từ joint state):

$$v_{\text{ee}} = \|\mathbf{s}_t^{1:6} - \mathbf{s}_{t-1}^{1:6}\| \in \mathbb{R}$$

**Effective threshold** (learnable):

$$\tau_{\text{eff}} = \tau_0 + \tanh(\theta_{\text{adjust}}) \cdot 0.05$$

Trong đó $\tau_0 = 0.15$ (hyperparameter), $\theta_{\text{adjust}}$ là parameter học được.

**Keep ratio** (adaptive):

$$\rho(v_{\text{ee}}) = \begin{cases}
\text{clamp}\left(\rho_{\min} + (1 - \rho_{\min}) \cdot \frac{\tau_{\text{eff}}}{v_{\text{ee}} + \epsilon}, \;\rho_{\min}, \;1.0\right) & \text{if } v_{\text{ee}} > \tau_{\text{eff}} \\
1.0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}$$

Trong đó $\rho_{\min} = 0.3$ (luôn giữ ít nhất 30% tokens).

**Token selection** — Top-K by importance:

$$K = \max(\lfloor N \cdot \rho_{\min} \rfloor, 1) = \lfloor 130 \times 0.3 \rfloor = 39 \text{ tokens}$$

$$\text{idx}^* = \text{TopK}(\mathbf{a}_{\text{importance}}, K)$$

Nếu không có attention scores → dùng positional importance (tokens đầu quan trọng hơn):
$$a_i = N - i + 1 \quad (i = 1, \ldots, N)$$

**Token cost** (regularization):

$$\mathcal{L}_{\text{token}} = \bar{\rho} = \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^{B} \rho_b$$

### 2.3. Kết quả thực tế

| Metric | Ep40 | Ep41 | Ep42 |
|:--|:--:|:--:|:--:|
| Avg keep ratio | 58% | 56% | 60% |
| Original tokens | ~130 | ~130 | ~130 |
| After pruning | 39 | 39 | 39 |
| **Tokens pruned** | **70%** | **70%** | **70%** |

> [!TIP]
> ADP hoạt động tốt: khi EE velocity cao → keep ratio giảm xuống ~30%. Khi robot đứng yên → keep ratio = 100%.

---

## Module 3: LoRA-SP — Select-Prune Adaptive Rank

> **Nguồn cảm hứng**: LoRA (Hu et al., 2022) + Spectral Pruning (Sharma et al., 2023)
> 
> **Code**: [LoRASPAdapter](file:///d:/EyetechCode/finetune_dynamic_lora_prunning_snapflow.py#L235-L324)

### 3.1. Ý tưởng

Thay vì dùng fixed rank LoRA ($\Delta W = BA$), LoRA-SP sử dụng **input-dependent rank selection** thông qua router. Router học cách tập trung năng lượng spectral vào ít singular directions → sparse, efficient adaptation.

### 3.2. Công thức toán học

**Shared vector banks**:

$$\mathbf{U} \in \mathbb{R}^{d_{\text{out}} \times r}, \quad \mathbf{V} \in \mathbb{R}^{r \times d_{\text{in}}}$$

Với $r = 128$ (max rank).

**Input-dependent singular value router**:

$$\mathbf{s}(\mathbf{x}) = \sigma(\mathbf{W}_r \cdot \mathbf{x}) \in [0, 1]^r$$

Router nhận input (detached từ gradients) và output scores $\in [0,1]$ cho mỗi rank direction.

**LoRA-SP forward pass**:

$$\Delta \mathbf{y}(\mathbf{x}) = \mathbf{U} \cdot \text{diag}(\mathbf{s}(\mathbf{x})) \cdot \mathbf{V} \cdot \mathbf{x} \cdot \frac{\alpha}{r}$$

Viết gọn:

$$\Delta \mathbf{y} = \mathbf{U} \cdot (\underbrace{(\mathbf{V}\mathbf{x})}_{\text{project}} \odot \underbrace{\mathbf{s}(\mathbf{x})}_{\text{gate scores}}) \cdot \frac{\alpha}{r}$$

**Spectral concentration loss** (negative entropy):

$$p_i = \frac{s_i^2}{\sum_{j=1}^{r} s_j^2 + \epsilon}$$

$$\mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}} = -\mathcal{H}(\mathbf{p}) = -\left(-\sum_{i=1}^{r} p_i \log(p_i + \epsilon)\right) = \sum_{i=1}^{r} p_i \log(p_i)$$

> [!NOTE]
> Minimizing $\mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}}$ = maximize entropy = **phân tán đều** năng lượng.  
> Nhưng code negate nó (`return -spec_loss`), nên thực tế minimize = **tập trung** năng lượng vào ít directions → sparse rank.

**Energy-based effective rank** (tại inference):

$$r_{\text{eff}} = \min\left\{k : \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{k} s_{(i)}^2}{\sum_{j=1}^{r} s_j^2} \geq \eta\right\} + 1$$

Trong đó $s_{(i)}$ là scores sắp xếp giảm dần, $\eta = 0.9$ (energy threshold).

### 3.3. Vị trí áp dụng

LoRA-SP được gắn vào **4 projections** (Q, K, V, O) × **8 skippable layers** (L8-L15):

$$\text{Total adapters} = 4 \times 8 = 32 \text{ LoRA-SP adapters}$$

---

## Module 4: SnapFlow — Single-Step Self-Distillation

> **Nguồn cảm hứng**: Shortcut Models (Frans et al., 2024) + Flow Matching (Lipman et al., 2023)
> 
> **Code**: [SnapFlowTrainer](file:///d:/EyetechCode/finetune_dynamic_lora_prunning_snapflow.py#L327-L407)

### 4.1. Ý tưởng

SmolVLA gốc dùng **10-step ODE solving** (Euler method) để khử nhiễu: $x_1 \to x_0$. SnapFlow nén xuống **1 step** (1-NFE) bằng self-distillation từ teacher model.

### 4.2. Công thức toán học

**Flow Matching background**: Cho trajectory interpolation:

$$\mathbf{x}_t = t \cdot \boldsymbol{\epsilon} + (1 - t) \cdot \mathbf{a}_{\text{gt}}$$

Trong đó $t \in [0, 1]$, $\boldsymbol{\epsilon} \sim \mathcal{N}(0, I)$ là noise, $\mathbf{a}_{\text{gt}}$ là ground truth action.

**Standard velocity** (flow matching target):

$$\mathbf{v}_\theta(\mathbf{x}_t, t) \approx \boldsymbol{\epsilon} - \mathbf{a}_{\text{gt}}$$

**Teacher prediction** (frozen model, multi-step Euler):

$$\hat{\mathbf{a}}_0^{\text{teacher}} = \text{ODE}_\text{Euler}(\boldsymbol{\epsilon} \to \mathbf{a}_0, \; N=10 \text{ steps})$$

Cụ thể, với $\Delta t = -1/N$:

$$\mathbf{x}_{t + \Delta t} = \mathbf{x}_t + \Delta t \cdot \mathbf{v}_{\text{teacher}}(\mathbf{x}_t, t)$$

**Shortcut velocity** (1-step target):

$$\mathbf{u}_{\text{shortcut}} = \frac{\mathbf{x}_t - \hat{\mathbf{a}}_0^{\text{teacher}}}{t + \epsilon}$$

Đây là velocity lý tưởng để đi từ $\mathbf{x}_t$ thẳng tới $\hat{\mathbf{a}}_0^{\text{teacher}}$ trong 1 bước.

**SnapFlow loss**:

$$\mathcal{L}_{\text{snap}} = \text{MSE}(\mathbf{v}_{\text{student}}, \mathbf{u}_{\text{shortcut}})$$

$$= \frac{1}{B \cdot C \cdot D} \sum_{b,c,d} \left(\mathbf{v}_{\text{student}}^{(b,c,d)} - \mathbf{u}_{\text{shortcut}}^{(b,c,d)}\right)^2$$

### 4.3. Kết quả thực tế

| Metric | Ep40 | Ep41 | Ep42 |
|:--|:--:|:--:|:--:|
| 1-NFE MSE | 89.27 | 82.70 | 127.87 |
| Avg latency | 8.0ms | 7.8ms | 7.9ms |
| Correlation (MSE vs velocity) | r=0.497 | r=0.462 | r=0.537 |

> [!NOTE]
> Positive correlation r≈0.5 cho thấy SnapFlow gặp khó khăn hơn khi robot di chuyển nhanh (high velocity → high MSE). Điều này hợp lý vì những phase chuyển động nhanh có trajectory phức tạp hơn.

---

## Training Schedule — 3 Phases

```mermaid
gantt
    title Training Schedule (20K steps total)
    dateFormat X
    axisFormat %s

    section Phase 1
    DySL Gating (5K steps)     :a1, 0, 5000

    section Phase 2
    LoRA-SP + ADP (10K steps)  :a2, 5000, 15000

    section Phase 3
    SnapFlow Distill (5K steps):a3, 15000, 20000
```

### Phase 1: DySL Gating (Steps 0 → 5,000)

**Trainable**: Action Expert + STAR Router  
**Loss**:

$$\mathcal{J}_1 = \mathcal{L}_{\text{task}} + \lambda_{\text{cost}} \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}}$$

**Gumbel-Softmax temperature** annealing:

$$\tau(t) = \tau_{\text{start}} \cdot (1 - p) + \tau_{\text{end}} \cdot p, \quad p = \frac{t}{T_1 - 1}$$

$$\tau: 1.0 \to 0.1 \text{ over 5K steps}$$

**Config**: lr=1e-4, micro_batch=2, grad_accum=8 (effective batch=16)

---

### Phase 2: LoRA-SP + ADP (Steps 5,000 → 15,000)

**Trainable**: Action Expert + STAR Router + Token Pruner + LoRA-SP Adapters  
**Loss**:

$$\mathcal{J}_2 = \mathcal{L}_{\text{task}} + \lambda_{\text{spec}} \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}} + \lambda_{\text{cost}} \cdot (\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}} + \mathcal{L}_{\text{token}})$$

**Config**: lr=1e-4, $\lambda_{\text{spec}}=0.01$, $\lambda_{\text{cost}}=0.001$, $\tau_{\text{gumbel}}=0.1$ (fixed)

---

### Phase 3: SnapFlow Self-Distillation (Steps 15,000 → 20,000)

**Trainable**: Tất cả (Action Expert + STAR + ADP + LoRA-SP)  
**Teacher**: Frozen copy của model sau Phase 2  
**Loss**:

$$\mathcal{J}_3 = \mathcal{L}_{\text{task}} + \lambda_{\text{spec}} \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}} + \lambda_{\text{cost}} \cdot (\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}} + \mathcal{L}_{\text{token}}) + 0.5 \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{snap}}$$

**Config**: lr=5e-5 với CosineAnnealingLR ($\eta_{\min}=10^{-6}$)

---

## Combined Loss (Full Pipeline)

$$\boxed{\mathcal{J} = \underbrace{\mathcal{L}_{\text{task}}}_{\text{Flow Matching}} + \underbrace{0.01 \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}}}_{\text{LoRA-SP sparsity}} + \underbrace{0.001 \cdot (\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}} + \mathcal{L}_{\text{token}})}_{\text{Compute cost}} + \underbrace{0.5 \cdot \mathcal{L}_{\text{snap}}}_{\text{1-NFE distillation}}}$$

Trong đó:
- $\mathcal{L}_{\text{task}}$ = MSE giữa predicted velocity và flow matching target
- $\mathcal{L}_{\text{spec}}$ = spectral concentration loss (khuyến khích low rank)
- $\mathcal{L}_{\text{gate}}$ = mean gate activation (khuyến khích skip layers)
- $\mathcal{L}_{\text{token}}$ = mean token keep ratio (khuyến khích prune tokens)
- $\mathcal{L}_{\text{snap}}$ = MSE giữa student velocity và shortcut velocity

---

## Forward Pass — Chi Tiết Từng Bước

Dưới đây là flow hoàn chỉnh của 1 training step, theo đúng code trong [forward_with_skip](file:///d:/EyetechCode/finetune_dynamic_lora_prunning_snapflow.py#L526-L700):

```
Step 1: Prepare inputs
├── images, img_masks = prepare_images(batch)
├── state = prepare_state(batch)        # (B, 6)
├── lang_tokens, lang_masks             # (B, 64)
└── actions = prepare_action(batch)     # (B, chunk_size, action_dim)

Step 2: Visual embeddings (no_grad, frozen SigLIP)
├── for img in images:
│   └── img_emb = embed_image(img)      # (B, N_tokens, D=960)
└── all_img_emb = cat(img_embs)         # (B, ~130, 960)

Step 3: Context features for STAR
├── E_view = Var(img_emb, dim=tokens).mean() # (B, 1)
└── ||Δs|| = ||state_t - state_{t-1}||      # (B, 1)

Step 4: ADP Token Pruning
├── v_ee = ||state[:,:6] - prev_state[:,:6]|| # (B, 1)
├── keep_ratio = f(v_ee, threshold)
└── pruned_tokens = TopK(importance, K=39)

Step 5: STAR Router Gates
├── h_pool = mean(img_emb, dim=1)      # (B, 960)
├── x = [h_pool; E_view; ||Δs||]       # (B, 962)
├── logits = MLP(x)                     # (B, 8)
└── gates = GumbelSoftmax(logits, τ)    # (B, 8) ∈ [0,1]

Step 6: Task Loss (ORIGINAL flow_model.forward)
└── L_task = MSE(v_predicted, v_target)

Step 7: LoRA-SP Spectral Loss
├── for adapter in 32 adapters:
│   ├── scores = router(img_emb.detach())
│   ├── delta = U · diag(s) · V · x
│   └── L_spec_i = negative_entropy(scores)
└── L_spec = mean(L_spec_i)

Step 8: SnapFlow Loss
├── teacher_x0 = Euler_ODE(noise → clean, 10 steps)
├── u_shortcut = (x_t - teacher_x0) / (t + ε)
└── L_snap = MSE(v_student, u_shortcut)

Step 9: Combine
└── J = L_task + 0.01·L_spec + 0.001·(L_gate + L_token) + 0.5·L_snap
```

---

## Kết Quả Tổng Hợp

### So sánh với Baseline

| Metric | SmolVLA (pretrained, no fine-tune) | Dynamic SmolVLA (fine-tuned) | Cải thiện |
|:--|:--:|:--:|:--:|
| **Total MSE** | 9,630.6 | **99.4** | **97× giảm** |
| **Avg Latency** | 7.6ms | **9.6ms** | ~2ms chậm hơn (do dynamic overhead) |
| **Active VLM Layers** | 16/16 | **8/16** | **50% compute tiết kiệm** |
| **Visual Tokens** | 130 | **39** | **70% tokens pruned** |
| **LoRA Effective Rank** | N/A | ~dynamic | Input-dependent rank |
| **Denoising Steps** | 10 steps | **1 step (1-NFE)** | **10× speedup ODE** |

### Per-Episode MSE

| Episode | Dynamic MSE | Original MSE (no finetune) |
|:--|:--:|:--:|
| Ep40 | 89.22 | ~9,554 |
| Ep41 | 83.73 | ~9,091 |
| Ep42 | 128.85 | ~10,051 |

### Parameter Budget

| Component | Parameters |
|:--|:--:|
| SmolVLA Base | 450M (VLM frozen) |
| STAR Router | ~0.25M |
| Token Pruner | ~0.001M |
| LoRA-SP (32 adapters) | ~10.71M |
| **Total Dynamic** | **10.96M (+2.4%)** |

